java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Atype>
public class GlobalAnnotationTypeRepository
extends AnnotationTypeRepository

The class that represents the task-level repository of annotations types available. If it is not closed, additional types may be added. This will usually be populated using the fromJsonDescriptor method.

findAnnotationType

public Atype findAnnotationType(java.lang.String label,
                                DocumentAnnotationTypeRepository docTypeRepository,
                                boolean hasSpan,
                                boolean create)
                         throws AnnotationException,
                                MATDocumentException
Find the specified annotation type in this global repository and copy it into the document-level repository provided. If no such type is found, and this repository is not closed, and the create parameter is set to true, then the annotation type will be created and added to both this and the document-level repository.
